  "texts": [
    "Language models capture morphological information implicitly during the pretraining process without the need for additional preprocessing steps such as stemming or lemmatization.",
    "Intuition: The tokenization process increases the efficiency of word representations because a model can reuse the same token to reconstruct similar words in a corpus of text.",
    "For example, the word civilization can be tokenized into civil plus ization.",
    "Reusing the second token can construct words such as modernization, optimization, realization, capitalization, generalization and hundreds of other words with that suffix.",
    "Tokenization also increases the efficiency of representing various word forms that represent the part of speech for a language."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}